entry.title: [signin] Fix crashes when reusing a signin tab
entry.content:
This CL fixes a issues when reusing a signin tab. In particular, the

`DiceTabHelper` is reset after sync was enabled, and it causes the

callbacks (enable_sync_callback_ and show_signin_error_callback_ to

be reset).



This causes crashes if the tab is later reused for another signin

event:

1) DCHECK in the constructor because of the missing error callback

2) crash if somehow the server would send a spurious ENABLE_SYNC

header. There is no reason the server would do this, but we should

still protect against this.



The fix is:

1) use the default error handling when the DiceTabHelper is reused

(same behavior as when there is no DiceTabHelper).

2) Ignore the ENABLE_SYNC directives from the server if there was no

flow in progress.



Fixed: 1471277

entry.title: Only touch affected PasswordFormManagers when processing predictions.
entry.content:
Currently, PasswordFormManager::ProcessServerPredictions loops over

both the new incoming forms and over all existing PasswordFormManagers.

This CL changes that behavior to only iterate over the new incoming

forms, match or create managers for them, and process their predictions.



The motivation behind this change (apart from just generally saving

work) is that Autofill is changing its prediction notification

mechanism. The new mechanism will call ProcessServerPredictions

separately for every new encountered form (instead of batching them).

entry.title: [Store] Fetch new file tasks for empty new selection
entry.content:
A CHANGE_SELECTION state change is handled by the TaskController. To

update the available file tasks, a CHANGE_FILE_TASKS action is sent off.



Previously, the CHANGE_FILE_TASKS was only sent for non-empty new

selections but this led to the bug of lingering file tasks from

the previous selection.



Change the code so CHANGE_FILE_TASKS is always sent for any new

selection.

entry.title: Add a helper class to more easily observe all AutofillManagers of a tab.
entry.content:
There is a 1:n relationship between WebContents and AutofillManager.

This means that AutofillManager::Observer consumers that wish to

listen to all events for a WebContents also need to implement

ContentAutofillDriverFactory::Observer to listen for driver creation

and destruction.



This CL aims to reduce the boilerplate needed to do the above.

Consumers can now implement AutofillManager::Observer, add a

ScopedAutofillManagersObservation member and not worry about anything

else.

entry.title: Remove 'absent' option from tab_strip.new_tab_button in the manifest
entry.content:
Previously tabbed apps could choose to hide the new tab button by

setting the following in the manifest:

"tab_strip": {

"new_tab_button": "absent"

}



The new tab button will also be hidden if the app adds a home tab

but does not change the new tab url (as the new tab button would

open the start_url, but that should be captured into the home tab).



Since there is no use case for hiding the new tab button when there is

no home tab, this CL removes the ability to get into that state.



This CL also removes the ability to set "auto" for

tab_strip.new_tab_button.

entry.title: [Promise Icons] Add promise_package_id to sync data
entry.content:
Add promise_package_id field to sync data. When the sync service

triggers an app installation on a device, we will create a promise app

item to represent the installation in the Launcher/ Shelf. We need to

check the sync data for the correct ordinal positions so that we can

place the item in the position in the Launcher/ Shelf. To know which

sync item we should read, we need a common ID between the promise app

item and the sync item. This common ID is the promise_package_id

field, which is the ID of an app package that is globally unique

across platforms. The Promise Package ID of an app is consistent

whether the app is installed or not. We cannot use the existing sync

App ID field for matching, since it can only be generated after an app

is installed (so a promise app item is incapable of forming one).



Bug: b/261907612

entry.title: DOM Parts speed optimization patch 3/N
entry.content:
This CL revamps several larger parts of DOM Parts:

- The PartRoot no longer maintains a list of unsorted parts. It

maintains a cache which is in sorted order, if it exists. If the

cache is dirty, then a call to getParts() will walk the full

sub-tree and collect the cached Parts.

- Several techniques are used to maintain the cache and keep it from

getting dirty:

1. A NodeMoveScope is used to maintain state during DOM tree moves

such as AppendNode or InsertBefore.

2. As Nodes are moved, if they can be removed from old PartRoots

or added to new PartRoots while maintaining the cache

correctness, that will be done. This uses information from

the NodeMoveScope.

3. This process is now also used to maintain the cache during a

Clone.

4. When walking the tree to re-collect Parts, each PartRoot now

returns a FirstIncludedChildNode and LastIncludedChildNode so

that the walk can be scoped to this sub-tree.

5. The cached Part list is now stored as a HeapDeque rather than

a HeapHashSet, and DCHECKs ensure that we don't ever need to

search the cache for a Part, so the HashSet isn't needed.

6. getParts() now returns a reference rather than a copy.



These changes are covered by the existing basic-dom-part-objects.tentative.html test.
